cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with establishing dense correspondences between a 3D object model and an image "in the wild" using deep learning. The paper also introduces a fully-convolutional neural network (F-CNN) for this purpose. 

The paper also involves the use of regression networks and semantic segmentation, which are common topics in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Additionally, the paper deals with landmark localization and part segmentation, which are topics that fall under the Graphics (cs.GR) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
